{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:51:40.970535+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e0f90ac88e1236616df18600c7f7a5f80ac113c6)", "id": "lc_87fbb0d6-5c8f-45d7-ab47-c92e961fd961"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom typing import Any, Dict\n\nfrom fastapi.security import OAuth2PasswordBearer\nfrom jose import jwt\n\nfrom app.services import BaseService\nfrom app.settings import settings\n\n# for authentication that works seamlessly with OpenAPI\nreuseable_oauth = OAuth2PasswordBearer(\n    tokenUrl=\"/api/v1/user/login\",\n    scheme_name=\"JWT\"\n)\n\n\ndef hash_password(password: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Creates a hash of the password\"\"\"\n    hashed_password = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.hash(password)\n    return hashed_password\n\n\ndef verify_password(plain_password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Checks if a password corresponds to a hash\"\"\"\n    password_is_verified = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.verify(\n        plain_password, hashed_password\n    )\n\n    return bool(password_is_verified)\n\n\ndef create_auth_token(payload: Dict[str, Any], expiry: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    This handles the encoding of user information into a token\n    that can be used. It is generic so as to accomodate access and\n    refresh token.\n    \"\"\"\n    expiry_delta = datetime.now() + timedelta(seconds=expiry)\n    data_to_encode = {\"expiry\": str(expiry_delta), \"data\": payload}\n    encoded_data: str = jwt.encode(\n        data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM\n    )\n\n    return encoded_data\n\n\nclass UserService(BaseService):\n    \"\"\"\n    This class helps perform bulk of activities required by the corresponding API\n    \"\"\"\n    def a_method(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Here, the use of `self.save` is demonstrated.\n        Ensure to take out this method.\n        \"\"\"\n        model_instance = ...\n        self.save(model_instance)", "id": "lc_427784b0-dbe8-4b24-8667-e9b4ace727cf"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b5c75cd2-c78d-4c9c-ba2c-e07bb69f24ab", "tool_call_id": "call_46d9e5ced8f24987a35c24c3", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:51:59.786119+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have enough information to explain how application settings are derived from environment variables. Here's the explanation:\n\n## How Application Settings Are Derived from Environment Variables\n\n### 1. Database URLs\nThe `app/settings.py` file reads PostgreSQL connection components from environment variables:\n\n```python\nDB_USER = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_USER\")\nDB_PASSWORD = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_PASSWORD\")\nDB_DB = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_DB\")\nDB_PORT = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_PORT\")\nDB_HOST = environ.get(\"POSTGRES_HOST\")\n```\n\nThese are then concatenated to form the database URLs:\n\n```python\nDB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{DB_DB}\"\nTEST_DB_URL = f\"postgresql+psycopg2://{DB_USER}:{DB_PASSWORD}@{DB_HOST}:{DB_PORT}/{TEST_DB}\"\n```\n\nThe `.example.env` file shows default values:\n```\nPOSTGRES_USER=sasori\nPOSTGRES_PASSWORD=sasori\nPOSTGRES_DB=akatsuki\nPOSTGRES_TEST_DB=hebi\nPOSTGRES_PORT=5432\nPOSTGRES_HOST=postgres\n```\n\n### 2. Token Settings\n- **SECRET_KEY**: Read from environment (`SECRET_KEY`)\n- **ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME**: Hardcoded as `60 * 30` (30 minutes)\n- **REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY_TIME**: Hardcoded as `60 * 24 * 365` (1 year)\n- **JWT_ALGORITHM**: Hardcoded as `\"HS256\"`\n\nThe `auth/services.py` uses these settings for JWT token creation:\n```python\nencoded_data = jwt.encode(\n    data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM\n)\n```\n\n### 3. Redis Configuration\nRedis settings have default values but can be overridden via environment variables:\n\n```python\nREDIS_HOST = environ.get(\"REDIS_HOST\", \"localhost\")\nREDIS_PORT = environ.get(\"REDIS_PORT\", \"6379\")\n```\n\nThe `.example.env` shows:\n```\nREDIS_HOST=redis\nREDIS_PORT=6379\n```\n\n### 4. Other Settings\n- **ALLOWED_HOST**: Read from environment\n- **DEBUG**: Read from environment, converted to boolean\n- **ALLOWED_PORT**: Read from environment, converted to integer\n\n### Environment Loading\nThe `docker-compose.yml` shows that environment variables are loaded from a `.env` file for all services (web, postgres, redis), ensuring consistent configuration across the application.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 801, "prompt_tokens": 9298, "total_tokens": 10099, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 274, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8832, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0009313752, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002345052, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00069687}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962701-yM8WikhV3LON6UukLcmT", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a6-2eab-7f03-b6c9-e825f3f2f3ec-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9298, "output_tokens": 801, "total_tokens": 10099, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8832}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 274}}}}]}}}
